        "subjectItemTitle": "COMS",
        "section": "5",
        "requirementNumber": "5.4.8",
        "page": 39,
        "text": "COMS Daily Calibration Drift Test: The Calibration Drift must be quantified and recorded at zero\n(low-level) and upscale (high-level) calibration drift at least once daily according to the procedures\nlisted in 40 CFR 60.13(d)(2) and pt. 60, Appendix B, PS 1. The zero and upscale calibration levels must\nbe determined using the span value specified in the applicable requirement. If the applicable\nrequirement does not specify a span value, a span value of 60, 70, or 80 percent opacity must be used\nunless an alternative span value is approved by the commissioner. 40 CFR pt. 60, Appendix F must be\nused to determine out-of-control periods for COMS.",
