        "subjectItemTitle": "Boiler No. 1",
        "section": "5",
        "requirementNumber": "5.10.35",
        "page": 49,
        "text": "The Permittee must comply with all applicable requirements of 40 CFR pt. 60, subp. A as follows:\n40 CFR 60.1(a)-(c);\n40 CFR 60.2;\n40 CFR 60.3;\n40 CFR 60.4;\n40 CFR 60.5(a)-(b);\n40 CFR 60.6(a)-(b);\n40 CFR 60.7(a)(1);\n40 CFR 60.7(a)(3)-(7);\n40 CFR 60.7(b)-(d);\n40 CFR 60.8(a)-(i);\n40 CFR 60.9;\n40 CFR 60.11(a)-(g);\n40 CFR 60.12;\n40 CFR 60.13(a)-(f);\n40 CFR 60.13(h)-(j);\n40 CFR 60.14(a)-(c);\n40 CFR 60.15(a)-(g);\n40 CFR 60.17; and\n40 CFR 60.19(a)-(f).\nA copy of 40 CFR pt. 60, subp. A is included in Appendix H.\nIf the standard changes or upon adoption of a new or amended federal applicable requirement, and if\nthere are more than three years remaining in the permit term, the Permittee shall file an application\nfor an amendment within nine months of promulgation of the applicable requirement, pursuant to\nMinn. R. 7007.0400, subp. 3.",
        "citation": "[40 CFR pt. 60, subp. A, Minn. R. 7007.0400, subp. 3, Minn. R. 7007.1150-7007.1500,\nMinn. R. 7011.0050, subp. 1(A), Minn. R. 7017.1010 & 7017.2015, subp. 2, Minn. R. 7019.0100]",
        "referencedIds": [],
