        "subjectItemTitle": "Fabric Filter - Low Temperature, i.e., T<180 Degrees F",
        "section": "5",
        "requirementNumber": "5.238.9",
        "page": 158,
        "text": "Recordkeeping of Pressure Drop: The Permittee shall record the time and date of each pressure drop\nreading, and whether or not the observed pressure drop was within the range specified in this permit.\nRecorded values outside the range specified in this permit are considered Deviations as defined by\nMinn. R. 7007.0100, subp. 8a.",
        "citation": "[40 CFR 64.9(b), Minn. R. 7017.0200, Title I Condition: Avoid major modification under\n40 CFR 52.21(b)(2) and Minn. R. 7007.3000]",
