        "page": 229,
        "excerpt": "Permit Issued: December 30, 2025\n11900002-103\nPermit Expires: October 6, 2026\nPage 229 of 611\nAppendix E. Boiler 3 NOX PEMS Plan\nAmerican Crystal Sugar Company\nEast Grand Forks\nBoiler No .3 Predictive Emission Monitoring System (PEMS) Plan for Nitrogen Oxides\nEmission Unit\nEU017/EQUI27 - Boiler No. 3\nNebraska Boiler, Inc.\nModel N2S-7-95\nConstruction Date: 12/31/1993\nCapacity: 200.1 MMBtu/hr\nFuel: Natural Gas\nRegulatory Applicability\nBoiler No. 3 was constructed in 1993 and is therefore subject to 40 CFR 60, Subpart Db, Standards of\nPerformance for Industrial-Commercial-Institutional Steam Generating Units.\nNitrogen oxide (NOx) emissions from Boiler No. 3 are limited to 0.10 lb/MMBtu per 40 CFR 60.44b(a). To\ndetermine compliance with the NOx emission limit, a performance test shall be conducted using a continuous\n\nPermit Issued: December 30, 2025\n11900002-103\nPermit Expires: October 6, 2026\nPage 230 of 611\nControl of the automated parameters directly affects fuel flow, combustion air, excess oxygen, combustion\ntemperature and residence time of the combustion air in the boiler furnace. Combined, these parameters\ndirectly relate to NOx emission levels.\nNOx Emissions\nAs per relevant guidance and applicable rules, performance testing for NOx was completed at three boiler\noperating loads, low, mid and high. This allowed collection of measured emissions over the range of\nprogrammed operations to develop a predictive operating curve. The most recent performance curve was\ndeveloped as part of the October 6, 2016 NOx performance testing. The table below lists the results of the curve\ndevelopment testing.\nTable 1. Performance Curve Development Data\nTest Run\nSteam Flow (pph)\nNOx (lb/MMBtu)\n68,215\n68,215\n0.055"
